'''拉奈島'''（{{lang-haw|'''Lānaʻi'''}} {{[laːˈnɐʔi，naːˈnɐʔi]}}，{{lang-en|'''Lanai'''}} {{IPAc-en|l|ɑː|ˈ|n|aɪ|,_|l|ə|ˈ|n|ɑː|i}})是[[夏威夷群島|夏威夷群島]]的第六大島，也是其中有公共交通可達的最小的有人定居的島嶼<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.latimes.com/business/la-fi-ellison-lanai-20120621,0,1109467.story |title=Oracle's Ellison to buy, invest in Hawaii's Lanai - latimes.com | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120624003746/http://www.latimes.com/business/la-fi-ellison-lanai-20120621%2C0%2C1109467.story |archivedate=June 24, 2012 }}</ref>。由於過去它有著全島範圍的鳳梨種植園，因此俗稱鳳梨島<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/9-crazy-facts-about-lanai-2014-9/?IR=T |title=存档副本 |access-date=2020-04-28 |archive-date=2021-03-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210314105911/https://www.businessinsider.com/9-crazy-facts-about-lanai-2014-9?IR=T |dead-url=no }}</ref>。島上唯一的城市是[[拉奈城_(夏威夷州)|拉奈市]]。

拉奈島是一個大致呈撇號形狀的島，沿最長方向的寬度為{{convert|29|km|mi}}。土地面積為{{convert|364|km2|sqmi}}，是[[美國島嶼面積列表|美國第42大島]]<ref name="SizeRef">{{cite web|url=http://www.hawaii.gov/dbedt/info/economic/databook/db2004/section05.pdf|title=Table 5.08 - Land Area of Islands: 2000|last=|first=|year=2004|publisher=State of Hawaii|accessdate=2007-07-23|archive-date=2012-02-29|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/65oFcgqlw?url=http://hawaii.gov/dbedt/info/economic/databook/db2004/section05.pdf|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。它的北面隔著海峽與[[摩洛凱島|摩洛凱島]]相望，東邊則是[[茂宜島|茂宜島]]。它的總人口從[[2000年美國人口普查|2000年人口普查]]的3,193人<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.census.gov |title=U.S. Census website |publisher=[[United_States_Census_Bureau|United States Census Bureau]] |date=2010-10-05 |accessdate=2013-06-17 |archive-date=2020-08-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200820053605/https://www.census.gov/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，減少到2010年的3,131人<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hawaii.gov/dbedt/info/census/Census_2010/demographic/demo_profile_cdp_NI/Lanaicity.pdf|title=Lanai city|publisher=State of Hawaii|accessdate=November 17, 2011|archive-date=2011-07-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110728020439/http://hawaii.gov/dbedt/info/census/Census_2010/demographic/demo_profile_cdp_NI/Lanaicity.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://files.hawaii.gov/dbedt/census/Census_2010/demographic/demo_profile_cdp_NI/Manele.pdf|title=Manele CDP|last=|first=|date=2010|website=Hawaii Government|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170215012821/http://files.hawaii.gov/dbedt/census/Census_2010/demographic/demo_profile_cdp_NI/Manele.pdf|archive-date=February 15, 2017|access-date=March 26, 2020}}</ref>。

2012年6月，[[甲骨文公司|甲骨文公司]]創辦人[[拉里·埃里森|拉里·埃里森]]以5至6億美元買下拉奈島98%的土地所有權<ref name="NYTM 2014/09/28">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/09/28/magazine/larry-ellison-island-hawaii.html|title=Larry Ellison Bought an Island in Hawaii. Now What?|work=The New York Times Magazine|last1=Mooallem|first1=Jon|date=September 23, 2014|access-date=1 December 2017|via=www.nytimes.com|quote=At a public meeting on Lanai last year, an Ellison representative explained that his boss wasn’t drawn to the island by the potential for profits but by the potential for a great accomplishment — the satisfaction one day of having made the place work. For Ellison, it seemed, Lanai was less like an investment than like a classic car, up on blocks in the middle of the Pacific, that he had become obsessed with restoring. He wants to transform it into a premier tourist destination and what he has called “the first economically viable, 100 percent green community”: an innovative, self-sufficient dreamscape of renewable energy, electric cars and sustainable agriculture.|archive-date=2021-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210319221718/https://www.nytimes.com/2014/09/28/magazine/larry-ellison-island-hawaii.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。其餘2％土地則仍屬於夏威夷州政府和部分私人住宅擁有者<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/08/23/us/lanai-a-hawaiian-island-faces-uncertain-future-with-new-owner.html|title=On Lanai, Tiny Hawaiian Island, a New Owner|newspaper=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|first=ADAM|last=NAGOURNEY|date=August 22, 2012|access-date=1 December 2017|via=www.nytimes.com|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112020054/http://www.nytimes.com/2012/08/23/us/lanai-a-hawaiian-island-faces-uncertain-future-with-new-owner.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/angelauyeung/2020/04/01/exclusive-larry-ellison-reveals-his-big-data-battle-plan-to-fight-coronavirus-in-partnership-with-trump-white-house/|title=Exclusive: Larry Ellison Reveals His Big Data Battle Plan To Fight Coronavirus In Partnership With Trump White House|last=Au-Yeung|first=Angel|date=|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01|ref=Forbes|archive-date=2021-03-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210314104833/https://www.forbes.com/sites/angelauyeung/2020/04/01/exclusive-larry-ellison-reveals-his-big-data-battle-plan-to-fight-coronavirus-in-partnership-with-trump-white-house/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

拉奈島上有一所學校，包含從幼兒園到12年級。拉奈市有一家醫院，有24張病床，還有一個社區保健中心，提供初級保健、牙科、行為健康和專業服務<ref>[http://www.mauimemorialmedical.org/our-family/lanai-hospital/default.aspx ''Lanai Community Hospital''] {{Wayback|url=http://www.mauimemorialmedical.org/our-family/lanai-hospital/default.aspx |date=20170607094028 }} Retrieved 30 June 2017.</ref><ref>[http://www.lanaicommunityhealthcenter.org/ ''Lanai Community Health Center''] {{Wayback|url=http://www.lanaicommunityhealthcenter.org/ |date=20180816065308 }} Retrieved 30 June 2017.</ref>。全島沒有紅綠燈。

